title: "UDSL v1.0 — Universal Document Structure Layer"
abstract: >
  UDSL (Universal Document Structure Layer) is a model-agnostic standard
  that enforces consistent document structure, reasoning schemas, tone routing,
  UX constraints, and terminology rules across AI-generated long-form content.
  It provides a canonical architecture for generating predictable, auditable,
  multi-model-stable documents using large language models.

